The paper focuses on computerized analysis of skin lesions using deep learning techniques, specifically fully convolutional networks (FCNs) for multi-class semantic segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a transfer learning approach to overcome data deficiency, which is a common issue in machine learning, indicating a possible fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of dermoscopic images also suggests a potential fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
